n to the role that local actors play in giving shape to individual BRI projects. The contributions in this volume provide both 'big picture' assessments of China's role in regional and global interactions and detailed case studies that home in on the role agency plays in BRI dynamics. Written by leading area studies scholars with diverse disciplinary expertise, this book reveals how Chinese efforts to recalibrate the world are taken up, challenged, revamped, and reworked in diverse contexts around the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 4aAsian Studies. 4aChina. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aInternational Relations. 4aInternational relations. 4aPolitical economy. 4aPolitics and Government. 4aScience and Technology. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh  aAgency.  aBRI.  aBelt and Road Initiative.  aChina.  aConnectivity.1 aFerchen, Matt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForough, Mohammadbagher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGhiasy, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzalez-Vicente, Ruben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuik, Cheng-Chwee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLinks, Stacey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLugt, Sanne van der, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMosquera Valderrama, Irma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPetkova, Mirela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relator